# ============================================================================
# public/_headers
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HOST-LEVEL SECURITY HEADERS (Cloudflare Pages / Netlify format).
#
# WHY here and not in next.config: a static-export site has no Next.js server to
# run the headers() function, so security headers are applied by the HOST. This
# file is honored by Cloudflare Workers Static Assets (the mechanism that serves
# this site) as well as by Cloudflare Pages and Netlify, applying these headers
# to every asset response. Verified live: every header below is present on
# production responses. It is the static-export equivalent of the canon Red/Blue
# (RB-01…RB-07) hardening — the protection is identical, just applied at the edge.
#
# When deployed to a different host, port these headers to that host's mechanism.
#
# SCRIPT-SRC NOTE: script-src intentionally includes 'unsafe-inline' and
# 'wasm-unsafe-eval'. This is REQUIRED by the chosen architecture, not a lapse:
#   - 'unsafe-inline': Next.js App Router (static export) emits per-page inline
#     RSC hydration scripts (self.__next_f.push(...)). They cannot be hashed
#     (content differs on every page, so no fixed hash list works in a global
#     header) nor nonced (a static export has no server to mint per-request
#     nonces). Without this, React cannot hydrate and the site renders blank.
#   - 'wasm-unsafe-eval': Pagefind compiles its search index as client-side
#     WebAssembly, which CSP gates behind this token.
# Residual risk is low on a static, first-party site with no server-side
# reflection of user input into HTML and React-escaped tool output (no inline
# injection vector). A stricter nonce-based CSP would require a Worker injecting
# per-request nonces via HTMLRewriter (a documented future hardening option),
# not something a static _headers file can do.
# ============================================================================

/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'wasm-unsafe-eval'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self'; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; form-action 'self'; upgrade-insecure-requests
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=63072000; includeSubDomains; preload
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), interest-cohort=()
